These are mindmaps for studying Linux kernel/driver, and most of the ideas came from the following three books. Thanks to the great authors!

Corbet, J., A. Rubini, and G. Kroah-Hartman. Linux Device Drivers (3rd ed.). O'Reilly & Associates, Inc., 2005.
Love, Robert. Linux Kernel Development. Indianapolis: Sams Publishing, 2004.
Daniel P. Bovet, and Marco Cesati. Understanding the Linux Kernel, 3rd Edition. O'Reilly, 2005.
